# Test goldens compared byte-for-byte against runtime `\n`-line output via
# `include_str!`. Without this, git's autocrlf on Windows munges them to
# `\r\n` on checkout and the byte comparison fails — see
# `crates/claude-mem-worker/tests/boot_context_golden.rs`.
crates/**/tests/fixtures/*.md text eol=lf
crates/**/tests/fixtures/*.txt text eol=lf
crates/**/tests/fixtures/*.json text eol=lf
